name: Telecommunications Service Priority
title: TSP
definition: Indicates the provisioning and restoration priority as defined under the TSP Service Vendor Handbook.
validEntry:
Nine Character TSP Control Identifier
One Character Provisioning Priority Level (E, 0-5)
One Digit Restoration Priority Level (0-5)
validEntryNotes: A TSP code ending in “00” indicates “revocation”, the removal of a previously assigned TSP code.
fieldNotes: These codes are assigned by the TSP Program Office.
